Britain anticipates an imminent statement from the IRA regarding a potential shift away from violence, as urged by its political wing.
This development is seen as a significant step towards a new era in Northern Irish politics.
Hopes are high for the IRA to announce a disarmament plan by the end of June, marking progress since the Good Friday peace deal in 1998.
Efforts to revive power-sharing have faced obstacles, with demands for IRA disarmament.
The IRA's response will be crucial in determining the future of peace in Northern Ireland.
